org.jruyi.io

Interface IFilterOutput


  • public interface IFilterOutput
    An output holder for a filter to pass the output to the next filter as an input.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void add(java.lang.Object output)
      Adds the specified output to the output queue as the final output corresponding to the input from previous filter.
      void more(boolean more)
      Used in IFilter.onMsgDepart(org.jruyi.io.ISession, O, org.jruyi.io.IFilterOutput) to indicate if there will be more outputs corresponding to the input from previous filter after IFilter.onMsgDepart(org.jruyi.io.ISession, O, org.jruyi.io.IFilterOutput) returns.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(java.lang.Object output)
        Adds the specified output to the output queue as the final output corresponding to the input from previous filter. All the output elements in the queue will be passed to the next filter one by one.
        Parameters:
        output - the final output corresponding to the input from previous filter
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified out is null

      • more

        void more(boolean more)
        Used in IFilter.onMsgDepart(org.jruyi.io.ISession, O, org.jruyi.io.IFilterOutput) to indicate if there will be more outputs corresponding to the input from previous filter after IFilter.onMsgDepart(org.jruyi.io.ISession, O, org.jruyi.io.IFilterOutput) returns.
        Parameters:
        more - true if there will be more outputs
        Since:
        2.1
